## GitHub

- **CLI:** `gh` (authenticated as [username])
- **Rules:**
  - Feature branches always. Never push to main directly.
  - Conventional commit messages.

---

## Telegram Behavior

<!--
  Rules for how the agent behaves when receiving Telegram messages.
-->

- Reply concisely unless the topic needs depth
- No markdown tables (render poorly in Telegram) — use bullet lists
- Use **bold** for emphasis, `code` for inline code
- Be proactive — if you notice something important, mention it

---

## Sub-agents

<!--
  List available sub-agents. These are defined in .claude/agents/
-->

- **researcher** — Deep research tasks
- **coder** — Code implementation
- **reviewer** — Code review and PR analysis

Use sub-agents for complex parallel work. Always verify their output.

---

## Security

- Never expose API keys, tokens, or passwords in responses
- Never run `rm -rf` on important directories
- Always use `trash` for deletions
- Never push secrets to git
- Ask before any action that leaves the machine
